n)\n\noutputData = util.load(\"results/output_Data.coffea\")","position":{"start":{"line":95,"column":1},"end":{"line":109,"column":1}},"key":"tBHhGjMzfj"},{"type":"code","lang":"","value":"\nThe second step of the analysis is to aggregate the `.coffea` files and convert them to ROOT. After you modify the code to remove the timestamp, we can write a Snakemake rule that depends on all the `.coffea` files and runs the aggregation script.\n\n```python\nrule make_root_files:\n    input:\n        # 1. We need ALL the group files to be finished\n        coffeas = expand(\"results/output_{group}.coffea\", group=ALL_GROUPS),\n        # 2. The script we just created\n        script = \"ttgamma_longexercise/save_to_root.py\"\n    output:\n        # The file expected by the next step (Combine)\n        \"RootFiles/M3_Output.root\"\n    container:\n        # We use the same container as the processing step\n        \"/cvmfs/unpacked.cern.ch/registry.hub.docker.com/coffeateam/coffea-dask-almalinux9:2025.9.0-py3.10\"\n    shell:\n        # Pass the output filename first, then all input files\n        \"python {input.script} {output} {input.coffeas}\"","position":{"start":{"line":110,"column":1},"end":{"line":130,"column":1}},"key":"jZ9p3OfCQK"},{"type":"heading","depth":3,"position":{"start":{"line":132,"column":1},"end":{"line":132,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Step 3: The Fit (Hybrid Environments)","position":{"start":{"line":132,"column":1},"end":{"line":132,"column":1}},"key":"ePJciik901"}],"identifier":"step-3-the-fit-hybrid-environments","label":"Step 3: The Fit (Hybrid Environments)","html_id":"step-3-the-fit-hybrid-environments","implicit":true,"key":"cpYEzgmOsn"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":134,"column":1},"end":{"line":134,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Now that we have ROOT files, we need to run the statistical fit. In this example, we use the ","position":{"start":{"line":134,"column":1},"end":{"line":134,"colum