"key":"oN7TLaima0"},{"type":"inlineCode","value":"Data","position":{"start":{"line":185,"column":1},"end":{"line":185,"column":1}},"key":"XEC1HXm93x"},{"type":"text","value":", ","position":{"start":{"line":185,"column":1},"end":{"line":185,"column":1}},"key":"rzDkMDwUMl"},{"type":"inlineCode","value":"TTGamma","position":{"start":{"line":185,"column":1},"end":{"line":185,"column":1}},"key":"Pfut8Ud6sx"},{"type":"text","value":", ","position":{"start":{"line":185,"column":1},"end":{"line":185,"column":1}},"key":"hvBTTmxBSp"},{"type":"inlineCode","value":"TTbar","position":{"start":{"line":185,"column":1},"end":{"line":185,"column":1}},"key":"vYuolWFJpc"},{"type":"text","value":", etc., using the Coffea container.","position":{"start":{"line":185,"column":1},"end":{"line":185,"column":1}},"key":"oM9ezfxis3"}],"key":"sYe47gtc7C"}],"key":"BUXS1We9HF"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":186,"column":1},"end":{"line":186,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Once all 8 finished, it ran the aggregation script.","position":{"start":{"line":186,"column":1},"end":{"line":186,"column":1}},"key":"uWM2jzZ1FT"}],"key":"iaeNoEZRIg"}],"key":"HiKMt9VeMW"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":187,"column":1},"end":{"line":188,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Finally, it switched to the Combine container and performed the fit.","position":{"start":{"line":187,"column":1},"end":{"line":187,"column":1}},"key":"aFETXdkfme"}],"key":"uGWhBKjCBw"}],"key":"s61SVYffhU"}],"key":"MhuPPSMUAf"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":189,"column":1},"end":{"line":189,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"You have just orchestrated a full HEP analysis involving Data, MC, Systematics, and Statistics with one command.","position":{"start":{"line":189,"column":1},"end":{"line":189,"column":1}},"key":"KiOC6tKV4s"}],"key":"fd2O6lPStG"}],"key":"HdruEJqd7f"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":192,"column":1},"end":{"line":192,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Comparing Snakefile with a Bash Script","position":{"start":{"line":192,"column":1},"end":{"line":192,"column":1}},"key":"TjqpvDzc8C"}],"identifier":"comparing-snakefile-with-a-bash-script","label":"Comparing Snakefile with a Bash Script","html_id":"comparing-snakefile-with-a-bash-script","implicit":true,"key":"ea9ngnozOz"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":194,"column":1},"end":{"line":194,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Let’s compare this with how you would do it in a bash script.","position":{"start":{"line":194,"column":1},"end":{"line":194,"column":1}},"key":"nl4xEdnK5V"}],"key":"Oa9mlXmON2"},{"type":"details","children":[{"type":"summary","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Full Snakefile for Reference","position":{"start":{"line":196,"column":1},"end":{"line":196,"column":1}},"key":"dml9s8U5Pv"}],"key":"VyVvdeXuOf"},{"type":"code","lang":"python","value":"# Define the groups (found in runFullDataset.py)\nMC_GROUPS = [\"MCTTGamma\", \"MCTTbar1l\", \"MCTTbar2l\", \"MCSingleTop\", \"MCZJets\", \"MCWJets\", \"MCOther\"]\nDATA_GROUPS = [\"Data\"]\nALL_GROUPS = MC_GROUPS + DATA_GROUPS\n\nrule all:\n    input:\n        \"fitDiagnosticsTest.root\"\n\nrule run_coffea:\n    input:\n        script = \"ttgamma_longexercise/runFullDataset.py\"\n    output:\n        \"results/output_{group}.coffea\"\n    container:\n        \"/cvmfs/unpacked.cern.ch/registry.hub.docker.com/coffeateam/coffea-dask-almalinux9:2025.9.0-py3.10\"\n    shell:\n        # We run with the modified script which outputs deterministic filenames\n        \"python {input.script} {wildcards.group} --outdir results --workers 1 --executor local --maxchunks 1\"\n\nrule make_root_files:\n    input:\n        coffeas = expand(\"results/output_{group}.coffea\", group=ALL_GROUPS),\n        script = \"ttgamma_longexercise/save_to_root.py\"\n    output:\n        \"RootFiles/M3_Output.root\"\n    container:\n        \"/cvmfs/unpacked.cern.ch/registry.hub.docker.com/coffeateam/coffea-dask-almalinux9:2025.9.0-py3.10\"\n    shell:\n        \"python {input.script} {output} {input.coffeas}\"\n\nrule run_combine:\n    input:\n        root_file = \"RootFiles/M3_Output.root\",\n        card = \"ttgamma_longexercise/Fitting/data_card.txt\",\n        container = '/cvmfs/unpacked.cern.ch/gitlab-registry.cern.ch/cms-analysis/general/combine-container:latest'\n    output:\n        \"fitDiagnosticsTest.root\"\n    shell:\n        \"\"\"\n        APPTAINER_SHELL=$(which bash) apptainer exec -B .:/home/cmsusr/analysis \\\n              -B /cvmfs --pwd /home/cmsusr/analysis/  \\\n              {input.container} \\\n              /bin/bash -c \"export LANG=C && export LC_ALL=C && \\\n              source /cvmfs/cms.cern.ch/cmsset_default.sh && \\\n             cd /home/cmsusr/CMSSW_14_1_0_pre4/ && \\\n             cmsenv && \\\n             cd - && \\\n            text2workspace.py {input.card} -m 125 -o workspace.root && \\\n            combine -M FitDiagnostics workspace.root --saveShapes --saveWithUncertainties\"\n        \"\"\"","position":{"start":{"line":197,"column":1},"end":{"line":248,"column":1}},"key":"tXUZNCOmZK"}],"key":"MIDvyKSyYT"},{"type":"code","lang":"","value":"\n```{dropdown} Full Bash Script for Reference\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\n\n# ==============================================================================\n# CONFIGURATION\n# ==============================================================================\nMC_GROUPS=(\"MCTTGamma\" \"MCTTbar1l\" \"MCTTbar2l\" \"MCSingleTop\" \"MCZJets\" \"MCWJets\" \"MCOther\")\nDATA_GROUPS=(\"Data\")\nALL_GROUPS=(\"${MC_GROUPS[@]}\" \"${DATA_GROUPS[@]}\")\n\n# Define Container Paths\nCOFFEA_CONTAINER=\"/cvmfs/unpacked.cern.ch/registry.hub.docker.com/coffeateam/coffea-dask-almalinux9:2025.9.0-py3.10\"\nCOMBINE_CONTAINER=\"/cvmfs/unpacked.cern.ch/gitlab-registry.cern.ch/cms-analysis/general/combine-container:latest\"\n\n# Fail on first error\nset -e \n\n# ==============================================================================\n# STEP 1: PROCESSING (Coffea)\n# ==============================================================================\necho \"--- Step 1: Running Coffea Processor ---\"\nmkdir -p results\n\n# We have to manually loop over every sample\nfor group in \"${ALL_GROUPS[@]}\"; do\n    output_file=\"results/output_${group}.coffea\"\n    \n    # MANUAL CHECK: basic \"target\" logic (skip if exists)\n    if [ -f \"$output_file\" ]; then\n        echo \"Skipping $group (Output exists)\"\n        continue\n    fi\n\n    echo \"Processing $group...\"\n    \n    # We have to manually invoke the container for EACH job\n    apptainer exec -B .:$PWD $COFFEA_CONTAINER \\\n        python ttgamma_longexercise/runFullDataset.py \\\n        \"$group\" --outdir results --workers 1 --executor local --maxchunks 1\ndone\n\n# ==============================================================================\n# STEP 2: AGGREGATION (Coffea)\n# ==============================================================================\necho \"--- Step 2: Aggregating Histograms ---\"\nmkdir -p RootFiles\n\n# We have to construct the list of input files manually\nINPUT_LIST=\"\"\nfor group in \"${ALL_GROUPS[@]}\"; do\n    INPUT_LIST=\"$INPUT_LIST results/output_${group}.coffea\"\ndone\n\n# Run the aggregation\napptainer exec -B .:$PWD $COFFEA_CONTAINER \\\n    python scripts/make_root_wrapper.py \\\n    \"RootFiles/M3_Output.root\" $INPUT_LIST\n\n# ==============================================================================\n# STEP 3: STATISTICS (Combine)\n# ==============================================================================\necho \"--- Step 3: Running Fit ---\"\n\nAPPTAINER_SHELL=$(which bash) apptainer exec -B .:/home/cmsusr/analysis \\\n    -B /cvmfs --pwd /home/cmsusr/analysis/ \\\n    $COMBINE_CONTAINER \\\n    /bin/bash -c \"export LANG=C && export LC_ALL=C && \\\n    source /cvmfs/cms.cern.ch/cmsset_default.sh && \\\n    cd /home/cmsusr/CMSSW_14_1_0_pre4/ && \\\n    cmsenv && \\\n    cd - && \\\n    text2workspace.py ttgamma_longexercise/Fitting/data_card.txt -m 125 -o workspace.root && \\\n    combine -M FitDiagnostics workspace.root --saveShapes --saveWithUncertainties\"\n\necho \"Analysis Complete!\"","position":{"start":{"line":250,"column":1},"end":{"line":328,"column":1}},"key":"oS81Aknoh0"},{"type":"code","lang":"","value":"\n### Key Differences to Highlight\n\n* **Parallelism**:\n    * Bash: Runs sequentially (one loop after another). To make this parallel, you'd need complex `&`, `wait`, or `GNU` parallel commands.\n    * Snakemake: Just add `--cores 4` and it figures it out.\n\n* **Resuming**:\n    * Bash: Requires writing manual `if [ -f file ]; then ...` blocks. If you change a script, Bash won't know to re-run the step unless you delete the file manually.\n    * Snakemake: Automatically detects if `runFullDataset.py` is newer than the output and re-runs only the necessary parts.\n\n* **Environment Switching**:\n    * Bash: You have to manually wrap every command in `apptainer exec ....`\n    * Snakemake: You define the `container:` once per rule, and Snakemake handles the wrapping.\n\n```{admonition} Keypoints\n:class: important\n- **Integration:** You can wrap almost any existing script in Snakemake, provided the Input/Output filenames are predictable.\n- **Determinism:** If a script produces random timestamps or unique IDs in filenames, you must \"patch\" it to ensure Snakemake can track the files.\n- **Hybrid Environments:** While `container:` is preferred, you can explicitly call `apptainer exec` inside a `shell` block when you need complex environment sourcing (like `cmsenv`).\n- **Orchestration:** Snakemake can seamlessly connect completely different software stacks (e.g., Python/Coffea and C++/ROOT/Combine) into a single reproducible pipeline.","position":{"start":{"line":329,"column":1},"end":{"line":351,"column":1}},"key":"MBHVnCAqxe"}],"key":"lyXNRdSIK2"}],"key":"ngKeEPfgxf"},"references":{"cite":{"order":[],"data":{}}}}